Description: Continue to execute test and evaluation activities to include Developmental Test (DT), Integrated
Test (IT), and Operational Test (OT). Administer associated government support required to ensure AIM-120
missile integration with Department of the Navy aircraft platforms (F/A-18 C/D/E/F/G, AV-8B and F-35), and
hardware-in-the loop facility operations.

FY 2026 Plans:
Develop and procure test resources required to meet test requirements and provide support personnel to
complete AIM-120 DT and OT events. Operate hardware-in-the-loop facility. SIP 4 begins with the IT and OT
flight test in the first quarter and follows on throughout FY 2026. SIP 5 and SIP 3 Tape 3 begin captive flight tests
to support software build requirements with SIP 5 beginning in the second quarter and SIP 3 Tape 3 beginning in
third quarter.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Develop and procure test resources required to meet test requirements and provide support personnel to
execute AIM-120 Developmental Test (DT) and Operational Test (OT) events. Hardware-in-the-loop facility
operations will continue.
FY 2027 OOC Plans:

