A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Real-Time Spectrum Operations (RTSO) program develops tools, processes, and algorithms to conduct spectrum planning, spectrum sensing, and monitoring
of the electromagnetic (EM) environment; characterize and predict electromagnetic (EM) environmental effects (E3); and manage and maneuver to avoid or mitigate
electromagnetic interference (EMI) and EM vulnerability of Navy platforms.

 RTSO supports Navy and Marine Corps EM Spectrum Operations for global spectrum usage and allocation planning. RTSO researches the effects between shipboard
 transmitters and receivers and EM system interactions with the other systems installed on units within a strike group. The program developed a capability to sense and
 monitor shipboard EM spectrum usage and provides information to validate spectrum plans in support of Emissions Control (EMCON) within the strike group. RTSO
 software validates and displays spectrum plan compliance with a spectrum common operational picture. This EM spectrum management aid, combined with an Own
 Force Monitoring (OFM) sensor input, supports Battlespace Awareness and Information Operations. These self-awareness and validation capabilities greatly enhance
 the Navy's ability to perform command and control of the EM spectrum warfighting domain.

 In FY 2027, the RTSO program will continue to develop and integrate new capabilities for RTSO OFM and spectrum management and design across various Navy
 and Military Sealift Command (MSC) ship classes. Research and development efforts will focus on enhancing RTSO software, including cloud architecture, spectrum
 management, and detection capabilities. Additionally, RTSO will explore proof-of-concept capabilities, such as spectrum mission planning decision aids and intelligent
 sectoring, as well as models to estimate Radio Frequency (RF) performance ranges in complex electromagnetic environments. The program will also participate in
 Limited Objective Experiments to demonstrate new capabilities to Fleet users and develop software releases for afloat users in a cloud environment. Furthermore, RTSO
 will validate machine learning and software automation capabilities to inform future integration and development.

