Description: This initiative enhances mission effectiveness by advancing capabilities in two critical,
complementary technology areas: resilient navigation and advanced materials. This program develops
advanced positioning capabilities by integrating diverse navigation references and multiple data streams,
thereby improving positional accuracy and system resilience for sustained, precise operations. Concurrently, the
initiative incorporates advanced materials into key system components to enhance performance and increase
survivability, leveraging innovative production methods to field more durable and capable systems. Additional
details held at a higher classification level.

FY 2026 Plans:
Funding for mission effectiveness is allocated across both unclassified and classified efforts. The unclassified
portion, totaling $27.289 million, includes the following tasks:
- Project Athena: Mature the capability to fuse data from multiple alt-nav sensors to provide a resilient navigation
solution
- Project MIDAS: Implement alternative navigation technologies on a prototype payload
- Project Scylla: Enable the trusted use of multi-Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS) signals for navigation
- Project Halcyon: Radar and algorithm integration for upcoming test flight
- Non-Line of Sight system: Develop a high-bandwidth, eye-safe, free-space optical communication system for
high data rate transmission
- Robust chip-scale optical beam positioning system: Capability to enable two-way communication between
bodies

