FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The requested $31.453 million funding increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is for critical guidance system
enhancements to ensure navigational superiority in contested environments. $19.973 million of this increase
is for classified efforts. The remainder will expand the Halcyon alternative guidance system, develop high-
bandwidth optical communications, and advance a quantum gravimeter for improved at-sea calibration. Funding
will also support a next-generation atomic clock for assured timing on extended missions and a partnership
with industry to produce hardened integrated circuits at commercial foundries, strengthening the domestic
industrial base. These initiatives directly increase system robustness and provide next-generation capabilities for
navigating in difficult environments. Additional details provided in the classified budget exhibit.
