D. Acquisition Strategy
The acquisition strategy includes development, integration, test, and qualification of the completely redesigned GEU-R which provides centralized housing of the
electronic cards for navigation, guidance, flight control, pyro & power control, mission control (MC), and secondary power and manages all missile monitoring and control
functions (navigation, communications, guidance, speed, attitude, health, component power application timing/activation of discrete events).




