D. Acquisition Strategy
The M-Code Increment I acquisition strategy includes the development, integration, test, qualification, and production of a new GPS receiver which will satisfy Public
Law 111-383, sec 913 compliance. Development includes the Tactical Tomahawk M-Code program co-developing the Common Architecture for Assured PNT (CAAP)
high anti-jam M-Code ASIC with USAF SDB-II Program Office. M-Code capability enables the missile to maintain GPS integrity in an enhanced spoofing environment.
M-Code Milestone B occurred in FY 2019. The M-Code program includes upgrades to the All-Up Round (AUR) missile, Tactical Tomahawk Weapons Control System
(TTWCS) v5.6.0/5.6.1, Submarine Combat & Control System (CCS), and also requires upgrade to the Theater Mission Planning Center (TMPC) program (under PU
4036).




