       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY2027 RDT&E request reflects a decrease of $1.036 million from FY2026 as the T-AGOS program transitions from higher-intensity Developmental Test
       Phase B activities into a more measured IOT&E planning and coordination phase. FY2026 funding supports drafting the IOT&E test plan, execution of cyber
       testing activities including a Cyber Tabletop Exercise, acoustic and RADHAZ analyses, and early planning for FY31 and FY32 execution. In FY2027, the program
       sustains essential IOT&E coordination and Calm and Rough Water Trial preparations, while deferring major test execution events to align with the actual program
       schedule. The reduced funding level reflects the completion of several upfront planning and analysis efforts in FY2026 and appropriately scopes FY2027
       resources to maintain momentum without prematurely frontloading test activities.


