FY 2026 Plans:
In FY2026, the T-AGOS program will continue Developmental Test (DT) Phase B and initiate preparation for
Operational Testing (OT), focusing on Cyber Testing Support and early-stage IOT&E activities. Key efforts
include drafting the IOT&E test plan, initiating acoustic and RADHAZ analysis, executing the Cyber Tabletop
Exercise, and beginning planning for FY31/FY32 execution. Engagements with OPTEVFOR, PMS 485, MSC,
and OPNAV will continue to align test objectives and support.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
FY2027 efforts will maintain momentum from FY2026 by continuing IOT&E coordination and Calm/Rough Water
Trial preparations. This level of effort ensures that planning and stakeholder coordination remain on track,
without frontloading major test events prematurely. Resources are appropriately scoped to align with the actual
program timeline and projected activities.
