lab facility improvements made in the first year of the program.
                                                                                 Accomplishments/Planned Programs Subtotals                 0.000       24.319        22.244$$, $$$$, $$The Teleport program will employ a balanced acquisition strategy to ensure both cost-effectiveness and the highest levels of operational security and mission assurance.
The program will utilize in-house contracting capabilities for critical integration and security requirements, leveraging the expertise of government personnel to maintain
control over these sensitive areas.

 For specialized components and commercial satellite services, the program will leverage competitive contracting processes. This approach promotes innovation and
 ensures access to the best available technologies at the most competitive prices.

 The strategy emphasizes phased implementation aligned with the FY26-FY27 timeline, utilizing agile development methodologies for software systems. For access to
 Low Earth Orbit (LEO) and Medium Earth Orbit (MEO) constellations, the program will leverage service contracts rather than pursuing proprietary satellite development.
 This approach allows the Department to capitalize on the rapidly evolving commercial satellite market and avoid the high costs and long lead times associated with
 developing and deploying its own satellite constellations.

 This strategy prioritizes modular, standards-based solutions that enable future technological insertion while maintaining government control over mission-critical
 elements.

