 The Shipboard Helo Handler-Extra Low Profile Replacement (SHH-II) is a critical system that provides for the precise, towbarless movement of helicopters within
 the confined spaces of Littoral Combat Ship (LCS) flight decks. The low-profile design is a key requirement, as standard handlers cannot operate underneath the
 low clearance of the MH-60R and MH-60S aircraft. These replacement units are required to support flight operations, safety, and maintenance for the MH-60R (Anti-
 Submarine and Anti-Surface Warfare) and the MH-60S (Utility and Combat Support) platforms by replacing legacy systems.

