 include PQDR analysis of water pump failures and integration of VRC-145 communications system.

 The Family of Material Handling Equipment (FMHE) program provides the Marine Corps with a comprehensive suite of platforms to ensure logistics, distribution,
 mobility, and survivability across all operational environments. The FMHE portfolio enhances logistics throughput by providing various loaders and forklifts such as
 the heavy-duty TRAM, the versatile Extendable Boom Forklift (EBFL), and the Autonomous Pallet Loader (APL) to move materiel from ship-to-shore and in garrison
 settings. Concurrently, the FCE program equips engineer units with critical construction and earthmoving capabilities through systems like the versatile Multi-Terrain
 Loader (MTL) and Backhoe Loader (BHL) for excavation, the heavy-duty Medium Crawler Tractor (MCT) for obstacle reduction, and precision platforms like the Motor
 Grader and Vibratory Compactor for infrastructure development. Together, these programs introduce modern, autonomous, and lightweight solutions that replace legacy
 systems and enable key operational concepts like EABO in contested or degraded environments.

