       Change Summary Explanation
       Financial:
       - FY 2027 funding increase ($83.3 million) Program Adjustments for Compact Variant (CV).
       - FY 2027 funding decrease ($2.144 million) for Rate and Misc Adjustments.

       Technical:
       - A significant reliability issue with the Government-Furnished Application-Specific Integrated Circuit (ASIC) System Service Processor (SSP2) was identified
       during operational testing of Operational Flight Software (OFS) 10.4. As a result, the fleet release of the AIM-9X-4 missile has been postponed until the
       deployment of OFS 10.5, which incorporates a software-based mitigation.

       Schedule:
       - SIP III Hardware & v10.4 software changed from 2nd quarter FY 2025 to 4th quarter FY 2025.
       - Added CV risk reduction, CV, & OFS 12.6X.
       - OFS 9.5 Fleet release changed from 4th quarter FY 2025 to 3rd quarter FY 2026 due to delay in Operational Test analysis.
       - SIP IV Hardware ECP changed from 4th quarter FY 2026 to 3rd quarter FY 2027 due to delay to Government developed Telemetry assets Electromagnetic
       Environmental Effects (E3) testing opportunities.
       - OFS 10.4 SW release cancelled due to a significant reliability issue with the Government-Furnished ASIC SSP2.
       - SIP III OFS 10.5 Software release changed from 3rd quarter FY 2026 to 4th quarter FY 2027 due to incorporation of software-based mitigation for the SSP2
       reliability issue.
       - OFS 11.6X has shifted from the 3rd quarter FY 2026 to 2nd quarter FY 2027 due to a delay in proposal submission and the prioritization of completing the OFS
       10.X series software for delivery to the fleet.


